# Main page purpose #

This is a **romantic greeting / celebration landing page** that shows multiple greeting cards, decorative animations, and a floating draggable video player.

### Branding / page setup

* Page title: **“My Heart's Greetings”**
* Custom favicon using `emoji1.jpg`
* Uses Google Fonts:

  * Playfair Display
  * Montserrat
  * Dancing Script
* Includes external libraries:

  * **Three.js**
  * **Particles.js**

### Visual theme

* Soft romantic color palette with pink, blush, gold, and light background tones
* Elegant typography with script-style heading
* Overall greeting-card / gift-style design

### Header section

* Main heading: **“For only you”**
* Subtitle: **“a smalla effort ,by a someone”**
* Heading and subtitle both use fade-in animation on load

### Greeting cards section

* Responsive grid layout of cards
* Cards are shown in a **multi-column layout on desktop**
* Switches to **single-column layout on smaller screens**
* Each card contains:

  * featured image
  * title
  * subtitle/date-like label
  * “Open Card” button
* Whole card is clickable
* On click, each card opens a new page or site in a new tab

### Individual card links/features

There are 4 visible greeting cards:

1. **Ramzan Mubarak**

   * image: `pic1.avif`
   * opens external page: `Ramadan.html`

2. **Eid Mubarak**

   * image: `0987.jpeg`
   * opens external Canva page

3. **Eid al-Adha**

   * image: `Eid al-Adha.jpg`
   * opens external HTML page

4. **Happy wala birthday**

   * image: `bdy.jpg`
   * subtitle: “for a cute princess”
   * opens local page: `untitled.html`

### Card interactions and styling

* Cards have rounded corners
* Hover lift effect
* Hover shadow enhancement
* Card image has bottom gradient fade overlay
* Gradient-styled rounded button inside each card
* Button grows slightly on hover

### Background animation features

* Full-screen **particles background**
* Floating animated heart icons across the screen
* Hearts are created dynamically with JavaScript
* Each floating heart gets:

  * random size
  * random horizontal position
  * random animation delay
  * random animation duration

### Particles.js interactivity

* Pink particle theme
* Particles are interactive:

  * hover effect uses **grab**
  * click adds particles using **push**
* Linked particle lines are enabled
* Random opacity, size, and movement are configured
* Retina display support is enabled

### Intro overlay / gate screen

* A full-screen interaction overlay appears initially
* Overlay darkens the entire screen
* It contains:

  * **“Begin the Magic ♥”** button
  * **“Begin the game ♥”** button inside a link
* Overlay is intended as the first entry point before showing the media player

### Game entry feature

* “Begin the game ♥” button links to:

  * `https://srj-source.github.io/game2.html/`

### Floating video player

* Hidden initially
* Appears after clicking **Begin the Magic ♥**
* Player includes a video element using:

  * `videoplayback (1).mp4`
* Video is:

  * looped
  * inline-play enabled
* Styled as a floating mini-player
* Has pink border and shadow
* Positioned fixed at the bottom-right initially

### Video controls

The floating player includes:

* **Play/Pause button**
* **Mute/Unmute button**
* **Close button**

Behavior:

* Clicking begin starts video playback
* If playback succeeds:

  * player appears
  * play/pause shows pause icon
  * unmute button becomes visible
* Play/pause toggles video playback state
* Mute button toggles muted state and icon
* Close button hides player and pauses video

### Draggable media player

* Floating video player is **draggable**
* Works with:

  * mouse dragging
  * touch dragging
* Dragging is disabled when clicking control buttons
* Cursor changes to grabbing while dragging
* Supports mobile touch dragging with `touch-action: none`

### Footer feature

* Footer text: **“Made with ♥”**
* Footer link points to:

  * `indexshutdown.html`

### Animation features

* Fade-in animation for heading/subtitle
* Floating heart animation
* Sequential card animation attempt on page load

### Notifications feature

* Requests browser notification permission
* If permission is granted, shows a notification:

  * title: **“Hello!”**
  * body: **“miss beauty!”**
  * icon: `/emoji1.jpg`

### Service worker / PWA-related feature

* Attempts to register a service worker using:

  * `sw.js`
* This suggests possible support for:

  * notifications
  * background features
  * offline behavior, depending on `sw.js`

### Mobile responsiveness

* Heading font size reduces on smaller screens
* Subtitle font size reduces on smaller screens
* Cards collapse into single-column layout on narrow screens
* Draggable player supports touch devices

### Technical / implementation notes visible from code

* There is a call to `setupMusicToggle()` inside `DOMContentLoaded`, but that function is **not defined in this file**
* Because of that, it may trigger a JavaScript error unless defined elsewhere
* Sequential card animation logic sets `card.style.opacity = '0'` inside timeout, which may not behave as intended visually
* Three.js is loaded, but **not actually used** anywhere in this file

### Summary of major frontend features

This page currently includes:

* romantic landing page design
* greeting card gallery
* links to multiple celebration pages
* animated hearts
* particle background
* intro overlay
* floating draggable video player
* notification permission + popup notification
* service worker registration
* footer navigation link







@1
Here are the features present in this frontend code:

### Main concept

This is a **heart-shaped memory card matching game** where users flip image cards and match photo pairs.

### Layout and UI features

* Full-screen game layout with a **dark black background**
* Centered game board inside a `.game` container
* Board arranged in a **custom heart shape**
* Decorative heading text:

  * “Match the photo pairs”
* Footer-style ownership/credit text shown at the bottom
* Hidden **surprise modal/popup** that appears after game completion
* Close button inside the surprise modal
* Restart button in the HUD

### Game board features

* Grid-based board with **9 columns**
* Empty grid cells are used to create the **heart-shaped card layout**
* Card size and spacing are controlled with CSS variables
* Board is responsive and scales based on viewport size

### Card features

* Each card is a button element
* Cards have:

  * front face
  * back face with image
* **3D flip animation** using `rotateY(180deg)`
* Matched cards stay flipped
* Matched cards get a slightly different shadow style
* Non-playable empty spaces are inserted where needed for heart design

### Memory game logic

* Images are defined in `pairImages`
* Each selected image is duplicated automatically to create pairs
* Cards are shuffled before rendering
* User can click cards to flip them
* Only two cards can be active in one turn
* If both flipped cards match:

  * they become permanently matched
  * matched pair count increases
* If they do not match:

  * both cards flip back after a delay
* Same card cannot be clicked twice as a pair
* Already matched cards cannot be clicked again
* Board is temporarily locked while checking a pair

### Progress tracking / HUD

* Shows **Moves count**
* Shows **Matches count**
* Updates dynamically during gameplay
* Restart button resets the whole game

### Surprise / completion feature

* When all pairs are matched:

  * a **surprise overlay modal** appears
* Modal uses fade/visibility transition
* Close button hides the modal
* The content area for the final reveal exists, but the heading/message is currently commented out

### Restart feature

* Clicking **Restart** fully resets:

  * flipped cards
  * matched cards
  * moves
  * matches
  * cheat state
  * surprise modal visibility
* Board is rebuilt with a new shuffled deck

### Cheat / hidden owner feature

* Secret keyboard cheat code: **A, B, C**
* When pressed in sequence:

  * the game auto-reveals and auto-matches all remaining pairs
* Cheat animation flips cards one pair at a time
* Cheat does not run if:

  * already running
  * game is already complete

### Accessibility-related features

* Board has `aria-label="Memory card game board"`
* Each card has `aria-label="Memory card"`
* Cards and buttons use semantic button elements

### Responsive design features

* On screens below 900px:

  * card size becomes smaller
  * side text size adjusts
  * spacing changes
* On screens below 640px:

  * body allows vertical scrolling
  * layout becomes more mobile-friendly
  * side text becomes static and centered
  * credit moves into normal flow

### Visual styling features

* Serif typography for main game text
* Sans-serif typography for HUD and modal text
* Rounded cards and modal corners
* Shadows for cards and popup
* Muted secondary text color support
* Hover effect on restart button
* Overlay background darkens screen when modal opens

### Configurable/customizable parts in code

* Developer can change:

  * image list in `pairImages`
  * heart layout in `heartLayout`
  * surprise modal message
  * displayed headings/copy
* Code checks whether enough image URLs are provided for required pairs

### Current content state

* Right-side heading is commented out
* Surprise modal message is commented out
* Only the close button is currently visible in the modal
* Images are expected as local files like `a1.jpg`, `a2.jpg`, etc.

